## Why Cleaning Order Matters After Renovation

Construction work leaves multiple types of contamination: dust, plaster residue, adhesives, and fine particulate debris. Cleaning in the wrong order spreads dust and forces surfaces to be cleaned repeatedly.

## Correct After Builders Cleaning Sequence

1. Ventilate the property
2. Remove large debris
3. Vacuum all surfaces (top to bottom)
4. Clean walls and high surfaces
5. Clean windows, frames, and ledges
6. Wipe cupboards and fittings
7. Clean floors last

## Key Areas That Trap Construction Dust

- Skirting boards  
- Window tracks  
- Radiators  
- Light fittings  
- Door frames  

## When Professional After Builders Cleaning Is Needed

Large renovations or multi-room construction projects usually require specialist cleaning equipment to remove embedded dust and fine debris.

